remarks.format: ## Remarks The most common type conversion is to and from a string type. The default implementation calls the <xref:System.Object.ToString%2A> method of the object if the object is valid and if the destination type is string. If this method cannot convert the specified object to the destination type, it passes a <xref:System.NotSupportedException> exception.
